
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes
class Person {
  +personID: int
  +phoneNumber: String
  +keywords: List<String>
  +institutionCode: int
}

class ResearchInstitution {
  +institutionCode: int
  +name: String
  +address: String
}

class ScientificArticle {
  +doi: String
  +title: String
}

class Authorship {
  +position: int
  +personID: int
  +doi: String
}

class PeerReviewedPaper {
  +citationCount: int
}

class TechnicalReport {
  - // No additional attributes specific to this class (all in parent)
}

class Publisher {
  +name: String
}

class Journal {
  +name: String
  +impactFactor: float
  +publisherName: String
}

class Review {
  +reviewerID: int
  +doi: String
}

class Subscription {
  +institutionCode: int
  +journalName: String
  +publisherName: String
}

' Relationships
Person "1" -- "0..*" Authorship : author of
Authorship "1" -- "1" ScientificArticle

ScientificArticle "1" -- "1" Authorship : has authors

ResearchInstitution "1" -- "0..*" Person : employs
ResearchInstitution "1" -- "0..*" TechnicalReport : publishes

ScientificArticle <|-- PeerReviewedPaper
ScientificArticle <|-- TechnicalReport

PeerReviewedPaper "1" -- "0..*" Review : reviewed by
Review "1" -- "1" Person : reviewer

Journal "1" -- "0..*" PeerReviewedPaper : publishes
Journal "1" -- "1" Publisher : published by
ResearchInstitution "1" -- "0..*" Subscription : subscribes to
Subscription "1" -- "1" Journal : subscribed journal

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:
- **`Person`** holds basic information about a researcher, including keywords and their institution.
- **`ResearchInstitution`** represents an EU-based research organization.
- **`ScientificArticle`** is the base class for both `PeerReviewedPaper` and `TechnicalReport`.
- **`Authorship`** captures the many-to-many relationship between `Person` and `ScientificArticle`, with position tracking.
- **`PeerReviewedPaper`** includes citation count and review relationships.
- **`TechnicalReport`** is always published by one institution.
- **`Publisher`** and **`Journal`** manage publication metadata, with journals being able to share names across publishers.
- **`Review`** links reviewers (`Person`) to peer-reviewed papers.
- **`Subscription`** manages which institutions subscribe to which journals.

